    {"instruction": "Identify this deck: 4 Price of Progress, 4 Lightning Bolt, 4 Chain Lightning, 4 Eidolon of the Great Revel, 4 Goblin Guide, 4 Monastery Swiftspear, Mountains", "input": "", "output": "This is Burn, a fringe aggro deck at 0.3% meta share. Every card deals direct damage to the opponent's face. Price of Progress deals double damage for each nonbasic land the opponent controls (devastating in Legacy where most decks run 15+ nonbasics). Eidolon punishes every spell costing 3 or less. The deck aims to deal 20 damage by turn 3-4 with no interaction. Budget-friendly at ~$1500."},
    {"instruction": "Identify this deck: 4 Veteran Explorer, 4 Cabal Therapy, 4 Green Sun's Zenith, Phyrexian Tower, various big creatures and planeswalkers", "input": "", "output": "This is Nic Fit, a fringe midrange-ramp deck. Veteran Explorer dies (often sacrificed to Phyrexian Tower or Cabal Therapy) and both players search for 2 basic lands. But Nic Fit benefits more from the ramp because it plays expensive threats like Primeval Titan, Uro, or planeswalkers that opponents' low-curve decks cannot match. Cabal Therapy provides hand disruption and a sacrifice outlet for Explorer. GSZ tutors silver bullets. The deck is a meta predator against fair blue decks but weak to combo."},
    {"instruction": "Identify this deck: 4 Enchantress's Presence, 4 Argothian Enchantress, 4 Solitary Confinement, 4 Sterling Grove, Elephant Grass, various enchantments", "input": "", "output": "This is Enchantress, a fringe combo-prison deck at 0.2% meta share. Argothian Enchantress and Enchantress's Presence draw a card whenever you cast an enchantment, creating a draw engine. Solitary Confinement prevents all damage and targeting (you discard a card each upkeep, sustained by Enchantress draws). Sterling Grove gives shroud to other enchantments and tutors. The deck creates an impenetrable prison where the opponent cannot deal damage or target you."},
